hilo-waikea.route_desc: This route operates between Mo'oheau Bus Terminal and central Hilo areas terminating at the Waiakea-Uka Gym.

hilo-keaukaha.route_desc: This route operates between Mo'oheau Bus Terminal and central Hilo areas terminating at the end of Kalanianaole Street.

hilo-kaumana.route_desc: This route operates between Mo'oheau Bus Terminal and northern and central Hilo areas. The route will travel to Kaumana Drive before returning back to Mo'oheau Bus Terminal.

hilo-volcano.route_desc: This route operates between Mo'oheau Bus Terminal and either Ocean View or Volcano. This route operates Monday through Saturday. Effective date of the schedule is September 26, 2012. Please be advised for passengers deboarding at Hawai'i Volcanoes National Park, there is a $12.00 per person fee to enter the park that is required to be paid at the gate (individuals 15 years and younger are free).   The ticket is valid for seven days.  Some days may be free to enter the park. For more information go to the Park website at; https: //www.nps.gov/havo/planyourvisit/fees.htm

hilo-pahala.route_desc: This route operates between Mo'oheau Bus Terminal and either Pahoa/Nanawale or Pohoiki/Leilani Estates. Three round trips on weekdays and two round trips on Saturday continue beyond Nanawale to Pohoiki, Sea View Estates Kalapana and Leilani Estates. This route operates Monday through Saturday.

hilo-resort.route_desc: This route operates between the Bayfront Park & Ride and the Mo'oheau Bus Terminal and South Kohala Resorts serving communities along the way. This route operates everyday, including all County observed holidays. The 3:50 a.m. trip to South Kohala Resorts, does not continue to Kailua-Kona on Sundays or holidays and will terminate at Waikoloa Beach Marriott Resort & Spa.

waimea.route_desc: This route operates within the Waimea area traveling between between Lakeland and Kamuela View Estates via Route 19. Destinations served on this route include Jacranda Inn, Hawaii Preparatory Academy lower campus, Parker School, Waimea Park, Long's Drugs, Parker Ranch Shopping Center, Kahilu Theatre, Kaiser Permanente, North Hawaii Community Hospital, KTA Super Stores, Waimea Civic Center, Kuhio Village, Kahele Oea and Lakeland. One trip will continue southbound to Hilo serving all communities along the Hmkua Coast terminating at Prince Kuhio Plaza via Mo'oheau Bus Terminal, County of Hawai'i Building, Aupuni Center, Hilo Shopping Center, University of Hawai'i at Hilo and Hawai'i Community College. This route operates Monday through Saturday.

pahala-kona.route_desc: This route operates between Pahala Shopping Center and Mauna Kea Beach Hotel or Kona International Airport at Keahole.

kona.route_desc: This route operates between Captain Cook and North Kona via Routes 11 19 and 190 traveling through Ali'i Drive.

kohala-resort.route_desc: This route operates one round trip between Kapaau and Hilton Waikoloa Village. Additional destinations served along Routes 270 and 19 includes: Hawi, Mahukona, Kawaihae, Kawaihae Harbor, Manua Kea Beach Hotel, Hapuna Prince Beach Hotel, The Fairmont Orchid, Manua Lani Bay Hotel and Bungalows, Waikoloa Village Marriott Resort & Spa, Queens Marketplace, Kings Shops and Hilton Waikoloa Village. This route operates Monday through Saturday as well as on holidays.

kohala-kona.route_desc: This route operates one round trip between Kapaau and Keauhou Shopping Center in Kailua-Kona. This route operates Monday through Saturday. On Saturday, this route DOES NOT serve Waimea.
